═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
  OPUS 4.7 vs 4.6 COMPARISON (our 215K-call dataset)
═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

  4.7 window: 2026-04-16+ (claude-opus-4-7)
  4.6 window: 2026-04-02 to 2026-04-15 (claude-opus-4-6)
  Testing: tokenizer inflation, Q5h burn multiplier, iter share

── SECTION 1: PER-CALL AVERAGES ────────────────────────────────────────

  Metric              |   Opus 4.6   |   Opus 4.7   | 4.7 / 4.6
  --------------------|--------------|--------------|----------
                Calls |        32299 |         2615 |     0.08x
     Avg input tokens |           40 |            4 |     0.10x
    Avg output tokens |          413 |         1079 |     2.61x
  Avg cache_read tokens |       103632 |       124086 |     1.20x
  Avg cache_create tokens |         5046 |         6894 |     1.37x
          Iter-call % |        57.9% |        78.8% |       N/A
        Iter-output % |        98.5% |        99.9% |       N/A

── SECTION 2: QUOTA PER CALL (cache_read = 1x formula) ─────────────────

  4.6 avg quota/call: 110,782 tokens
  4.7 avg quota/call: 136,380 tokens
  Multiplier: 1.23x

  ArkNill claim: adaptive thinking → 2.4x averaged Q5h burn.
  DO NOT USE this aggregate multiplier as corroboration or refutation.
  See Section 3 daily breakdown and Key Findings #2: the per-call
  multiplier here is confounded with workload-mix variance between the
  4.6 comparison window (Apr 2-15) and the 4.7 window (Apr 16-21).

